= class Gtk::SourceMarker

A source marker.

== Object Hierarchy

* Object
  * GLib::Instantiatable
    * GLib::Object
      * Gtk::SourceMarker

== Class Methods

--- Gtk::SourceMarker.new

     * Returns: self: ((*FIXME*))

== Instance Methods

--- buffer

    This method returns the buffer associated with this marker, as a Gtk::SourceBuffer object.
    * Returns: the buffer associated with this marker, as a Gtk::SourceBuffer object.

--- line

    This method returns the line number of this marker.
    * Returns: the line number of this marker.

--- marker_type

    This method returns the type of the marker.
    * Returns: the type of the marker.

--- marker_type=(type)

    Sets the type of the marker.
    * type: the type of the marker (as a string).  
    * Returns: the given parameter 'type'.

--- marker_type=(type)

    Sets the type of the marker.
    * type: the type of the marker (as a string).  
    * Returns: the given parameter 'type'.

--- name

    This method returns the name of this marker.
    * Returns: the name of this marker.

--- next

    This method returns the next Gtk::SourceMarker after the marker.
    * Returns: the next Gtk::SourceMarker after the marker.

--- prev

    This method returns the previous Gtk::SourceMarker before the marker.
    * Returns: the previous Gtk::SourceMarker before the marker.

--- set_marker_type(type)

    Sets the type of the marker.
    * type: the type of the marker (as a string).  
    * Returns: self.

--- deleted?

     * Returns: self: ((*FIXME*))

--- left_gravity?

    Gets the value whether the mark has left gravity or not.
     * Returns: true if the mark has left gravity

--- set_visible

     * Returns: self: ((*FIXME*))

--- visible=

     * Returns: self: ((*FIXME*))

--- visible?

     * Returns: self: ((*FIXME*))

== Properties

--- left-gravity: true or false (Read/Write)

    Whether the mark has left gravity

--- name: String (Read/Write)

    Mark name

